<p>##Introduction</p>

<p>Metrics are the properties of a data set that can be measured, aggregated, and compared.</p>

<p><strong>Notes</strong>:</p>

<ul>
  <li><em>Each data set is created initially with a single default metric, ‚ÄúRequestCount.‚Äù</em></li>
  <li><em>The ‚ÄúRequestCount‚Äù metric is the measure for the number of transactions, or orders in this example.</em></li>
  <li><em>The ‚ÄúRequestCount‚Äù metric can be deleted.</em></li>
</ul>

<p><a href="#top">back to top</a></p>

<p>##Configuration Options</p>

<p>###Dataset Metric Details</p>

<p>To view Metric Details:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Click on the <strong>Datasets</strong> tab.</li>
  <li>Click on a Dataset list (e.g. <em>Shared</em>).</li>
  <li>For the Dataset you wish to view Dataset Metrics for, click on the <strong>Dataset Name</strong> at the top of the corresponding card.</li>
  <li>On the <em>Dataset Details</em> Menu displayed on the left side of the screen, click on <strong>Metrics</strong>.<br />
All Metrics for the currently displayed Dataset are shown.</li>
</ol>

<p>###Metric Types</p>

<ul>
  <li>Count</li>
  <li>Time</li>
  <li>Size</li>
  <li>Number</li>
  <li>Currency</li>
</ul>

<p>###Metric Aggregations</p>

<ul>
  <li>Average</li>
  <li>Sum</li>
  <li>Minimum</li>
  <li>Maximum</li>
  <li>First</li>
  <li>Last</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="#top">back to top</a></p>

<p>##Configuration</p>

<p>###Add A New Dimension</p>

<ol>
  <li>Click on the <strong>Datasets</strong> tab.</li>
  <li>Click on a Dataset list (e.g. <em>Shared</em>).</li>
  <li>For the Dataset you wish to view Dataset Metrics for, click on the <strong>Dataset Name</strong> at the top of the corresponding card.</li>
  <li>On the <em>Dataset Details</em> Menu displayed on the left side of the screen, click on <strong>Metrics</strong>.<br />
All Metrics for the currently displayed Dataset are shown.</li>
  <li>Click the <strong>New Metric</strong> button in the upper right corner of the screen.</li>
  <li>Enter a <strong>Name</strong> and  <strong>Description</strong> for the new Metric.</li>
  <li>Use the <strong>Type</strong> drop-down menu to assign a type to the new Metric.</li>
  <li>Click on the <strong>Aggregations</strong> pull-down menu button to reveal a list of possible aggregation types to assign to the new Metric.  Multiple selections are possible.</li>
  <li>(Optional) Specify a <strong>Default</strong>.</li>
  <li>(Optional) Click the <strong>Mark as Required</strong> checkbox.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.<br />
The new Metric is saved and a corresponding row will be appended to the Metrics list on the <em>Details</em> page for this Dataset.</li>
  <li>(Optional) Click <strong>Cancel</strong> to exit without saving.</li>
</ol>

<p>###Modify Metric</p>

<ol>
  <li>Click on the <strong>Datasets</strong> tab.</li>
  <li>Click on a Dataset list (e.g. <em>Shared</em>).</li>
  <li>For the Dataset you wish to view Dataset Metric for, click on the <strong>Dataset Name</strong> at the top of the corresponding card.</li>
  <li>On the <em>Dataset Details</em> Menu displayed on the left side of the screen, click on <strong>Metrics</strong>.<br />
All Metrics for the currently displayed Dataset are shown.</li>
  <li>For the Metric you wish to modify, click the <strong>Functions</strong> pull-down menu, located at the far right of the corresponding row in the Dimensions list on the <em>Details</em> page for the Dataset.</li>
  <li>(Optional) Select <strong>Edit</strong>.<br />
The <em>Edit Metric</em> pop up window is displayed where you can modify the Metric‚Äôs Description, Type, Group, and assigned Aggregations.</li>
  <li>(Optional) Select <strong>Delete</strong>.<br />
The Metric is removed from the system.</li>
</ol>

